brewery.brewery_description: Triplehorn Brewing Co. another GREAT WA brewery! Our intent is to quench the thirst of the masses. We won't compromise the traditions of true beer styles. We will, however, work to create some very distinctive new versions! If you have a malty, hoppy, silky big beer desire, you'll find it here. Our taproom gives full vantage of the brewing experience. Come for the beer; enjoy the brash, bold, and often audacious intimacy. We may even write your name on the runestones of Valhalla. "For men of consequence a mound should be raised to their memory, and for all other warriors who had been distinguished for manhood a standing stone, a custom that remained long after Odin's time"

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description: This New England style fresh hop IPA packs a punch! Fruity, juicy aromas with a slight citrus kick that is complimented by the hazy goodness of a New England IPA. This double doesn't disappoint at 8-9% yet maintains an easy drinkability with relatively low IBU's. This beer was named after Moxee, WA and Rich VanHorn of VanHorn farms where we got our fresh hops.
